      <bioghist id="aspace_9f6f4db143ec3230ab9b2e5b19691df0">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The New Haven Hospital was founded in 1826 as the General Hospital Society of Connecticut. It was affilated with the Medical Institution of Yale College and served as the primary teaching hospital for the Yale medical school. Its name was changed to New Haven Hospital in 1884.</p>
      </bioghist>
